** About Godesta: **

GoDesta helps transport operators in the road freight industry optimise their
delivery of services, achieving greater efficiency from their fleets. An
essential part of GoDesta’s mission is to provide a reliable and user-friendly
experience allowing staff and subcontractors at transport operators to:

  * experience a shorter learning curve in using our solution; 
  * obtain greater insight into their fleet operations; and 
  * achieve greater efficiency whilst meeting their commitment to delivering safely. 

Your consideration of users’ needs and the application of your skill and
effort to provide an excellent user experience and contribute reliable,
maintainable code are a core part of GoDesta’s vision.

** About you: **

Due to aggressive growth, GoDesta is now looking for an ** experienced front
ent web developer and a junior front end developer ** to join our growing
product development team, constructing an industry leading SAAS product
servicing the road freight industry.

To be considered for this exciting opportunity, you will be a developer
working across all aspects of the development lifecycle, enjoy building
quality code and being included in the teams’ decision making process.  
  
_ Required: _

  * Demonstrated ability as a web developer, including HTML, CSS & JS, including considerable experience with at least one JS framework (eg React, Vue or Angular). 
  * Excellent communication skills (both written & verbal). 
  * Excellent prior employment history (in this or another field), demonstrating your reliability, enthusiasm and ability to work well with your colleagues. 
  * An enthusiastic attitude with a willingness to learn new concepts and progressively improve your skills. 

_ Highly regarded / desirable: _

  * Relevant tertiary qualifications focused on web development, such as Information Technology, Multimedia Design or a related field (eg computer science). 
  * Alternatively, evidence of completion of a comprehensive online learning program or coding bootcamp would be highly regarded. 
  * Understanding of the UX/UI design process. 
  * Experience working in AGILE environments, using task management tools such as Jira. 
  * Experience with version control, such as git or svn. 
  * Experience working with WebSocket protocol. 
  * Experience with mobile app development, including Flutter (helpful but not required). 

** Working at GoDesta: **

GoDesta is made up of a small team of developers, working together to deliver
excellent solutions to the transport industry.  
  
As part of a small team:

  * you will work primarily from GoDesta’s Brisbane office; 
  * your individuality and contribution will be valued; 
  * you will often work directly with key stakeholders, providing the opportunity to see how your creations shape the user experience; 
  * you will have the opportunity to work on a diverse range of features and technologies, demonstrating your creativity and enhancing your experience; 
  * you will have the opportunity to participate in and contribute to system design discussions; and 
  * you will have the opportunity to receive mentoring and feedback from experienced colleagues. 

** What to include in your application: **

  * A cover letter outlining why this role is right for you (don’t be afraid to be different) 
  * Your CV, including a detailed description of previous relevant projects you have undertaken 
  * A copy of any relevant tertiary qualification (or evidence of having completed education relevant to your work in this field) 
  * Confirmation that your citizenship or residency status permits you to accept employment in Australia (this will be verified) 
  * A link to your public github repository (if you maintain one and it contains any relevant material demonstrating your skills and abilities in this area) 

** Note: Applicants will be required to undergo testing to confirm their suitability, including completion of coding exercises in controlled conditions ** 

Applications close COB 2nd April 2024.

